Foot and mouth disease, Bulgaria
---------------------------------
Information received on 6 Apr 2011 from Mr Nikola T. Belev, President
of OIE's regional commission for Europe, delegate to the OIE, OIE
Regional representation for Europe, Sofia, Bulgaria

Summary
Report type: Follow-up report No. 9
Start date: 4 Jan 2011 [According to WRLFMD genotyping report, the
1st case, a wild boar, was shot in Kosti on 30 Dec 2010].
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 4 Jan 2011
Report date: 4 Apr 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 6 Apr 2011
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: October 1996
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: O
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Bliznak, Malko Turnovo municipality, Burgas
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Apr 2011
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
